  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nThere are several scenarios of navigation in app which may lead to bug when subsequent receiving messages won't have unread indicator (and message won't be visible in chat - see first scenario below)\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nUnread indicator is visible always when message received in chat until user has opened chat view when message received.\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nNo unread indicator is visible when message received in chat and user on different view (e.g. Wallet/Profile)\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/114703752-5d0b2500-9d2e-11eb-830e-1bd0ddf3f5d6.mov\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNote: this moved separately from https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/11895\r\n\r\n### Reproduction 1\r\n\r\n* UserA and UserB joins same public chat (or group)\r\n* UserB sends text message in public chat\r\n* UserA taps UserB user icon to navigate to itâ€™s profile -> and tap Chat from there to open 1-1\r\n* UserB now sends again in public chat message(s)\r\n* UserA navigates back to Chats\r\n* UserA opens public chat where unread message + unread indicator displayed\r\n**Actual result:** Message is not visible\r\n* UserA returns back to Chats view\r\n**Actual result:** Unread message indicator still displayed\r\n\r\n### Reproduction 2\r\n\r\n* UserA and UserB joins same public chat (or group or 1-1 chat) and stays on this chat view\r\n* UserA navigates back Chats main view by tapping 'Chats' tab button (Note: taping upon any tab button navigates user to main tab view disregard where he was before)\r\n* UserB sends message in chat\r\n* UserA checks if unread message indicator appears\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- Status version: develop 1.12, release 1.12.2\r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS \r\n",
